 <text>
  <front>
   <head>ODE.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">THE charms which blooming Beauty shows</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">From faces heavenly fair,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">W to the lily and the rose</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">With semblance apt compare:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With semblance apt; for ah! how soon,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">How soon they all decay!</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The lily droops, the rose is gone,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And beauty fades away.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But when bright Virtue shines confess'd,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">With sweet Discretion join'd;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When Mildness calms the peaceful breast,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Wisdom guides the mind;</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When charms like these, dear Maid, conspire</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Thy person to approve,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">They kindle generous, chaste desire,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And everlasting love.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Beyond the reach of Time or Fate,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">These graces shall endure,</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Still like the passion they create,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Eternal, constant, pure.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
